# GitHub Actions

## Workflows

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `sync-upstream.yml` | Incremental sync: `repository_dispatch`, hourly cron, daily cron, manual |
| `sync-bootstrap.yml` | Manual full history replay only |
| `sync-rebuild.yml` | Manual clean replay |
| `sync-verify.yml` | Scheduled dry-run verification |

## Mirror repos (separate repositories)

| Mirror | Upstream |
|--------|----------|
| `msys2-apiss/MSYS2-packages` | `msys2/MSYS2-packages` |
| `msys2-apiss/MINGW-packages` | `msys2/MINGW-packages` |

Branch layout: **`sync`** (default) holds workflow YAML only; **`master`** is a
pure fast-forward copy of upstream `master` (no workflow commits on master).

Templates: `docs/examples/mirror-sync.yml`, `docs/examples/mirror-dispatch.yml`.
Install both under `sync/.github/workflows/`. Set `UPSTREAM_REPO` variable and
`SYNC_DISPATCH_TOKEN` secret on each mirror repo.

## Runner

- Prefer `ubuntu-latest` with `actions/setup-node@v4` and Node.js 22.18+.
- Run `yarn install --frozen-lockfile` before running sync commands.

## Concurrency

```yaml
concurrency:
  group: sync-upstream
  cancel-in-progress: true
```

## Secrets

- `MSYS2_APISS_SYNC_TOKEN`: write access to `msys2-apiss/msys2-apiss` and this repo
- `SYNC_DISPATCH_TOKEN`: mirror repos only; dispatch `msys2-apiss-sync`
- Never log tokens; pass via `env:` to script steps only.

## Push policy

- Push destination branches `upstream`, `upstream-ports`, and
  `upstream-ports-mingw`.
- Track cursors in destination branches, not a committed sync state file.
- Skip destination push when script reports no new commits.
- Use bot identity: `github-actions[bot]`.

## Permissions

```yaml
permissions:
  contents: read   # this repo
```

Destination clone/push uses PAT secret, not `GITHUB_TOKEN` write to other repos.
